Pliny gives his architect a commission to rebuild a temple of Ceres on one of his estates, and to add porticoes near it.

Velim ergo emas quattuor marmoieas columnas cuius¹ tibi videbitur generis, emas 10 marmora, quibus solum, quibus parietes excolantur Erit etiam vel faciendum vel emendum ipsius deae signum, quia antiquum illude ligno quibusdam sui partibus vetustate truncatum est.
